@blocker missing_input_parameter_type
type: missing_parameter
mode: extraction
area: public_interface
status: valid
decision: Define the exact input parameter type for the log_sigmoid function.
fingerprint: input-parameter-type
prohibited: const Expression& | const reference
desc: The public interface defines the function name and output, but omits the exact type and const-correctness of the input parameter.
resolution: The input parameter must be of type const Expression& x.
q: What is the exact type of the input parameter for log_sigmoid?
q: Should the input be a const Expression reference or passed by value?
q: Does log_sigmoid take a single Expression or a vector of Expressions?
gt.omitted: The input parameter type const Expression& x for the log_sigmoid function.
gt.why: Without the exact parameter type, the agent cannot know whether to use a const reference, value, or a vector of expressions, leading to compilation failures or API mismatches.

@blocker missing_python_binding_files
type: missing_parameter
mode: injection
area: requirements
status: valid
decision: Identify which Python binding files must be updated to expose the new operation.
fingerprint: python-binding-files
prohibited: _dynet.pxd | _dynet.pyx | Cython
desc: The requirements mandate exposing the new operation to Python users, but omit the specific Cython binding files that must be updated.
resolution: Update the Python bindings in python/_dynet.pxd and python/_dynet.pyx.
q: Which Cython binding files need to be updated?
q: Do I need to add log_sigmoid to _dynet.pxd and _dynet.pyx?
q: Where are the Python wrappers located for the expression API?
gt.omitted: The specific Python binding files (python/_dynet.pxd and python/_dynet.pyx) that must expose the operation.
gt.why: An agent cannot guess whether to update pybind11, SWIG, or Cython files, nor know the exact file names in the python directory without explicit instruction.

